Colour: Body brown. Mandibles light yellow, antennae and apices of femur, basal area of tibia and whitish, tarsomeres dark brown (
Figure 3a
).

Legs: Tarsal claws with short tooth. (
Figure 5e
).

Gall: In staminate flowers of catkin inflorescences. Single-chambered (monothalamous), often in clusters, smooth centre with trichomes on the border, golden yellow colour and oblong/oval shape. No larger than 1.2 mm. (
Figure 3b
).

Colour: Mostly brown, tarsi, scape, pedicel and the first two antennal segments light yellow. Structure and sculptures as the sexual generation (
Figure 3c
) with the following differences: 12 antennal segments, ocelli not raised and tarsal claw almost simple.
